Andy Murray and Maria Sharapova suffered second successive defeat in the International Premier Tennis League.

The pair were beaten 6-1 by doubles specialists Rohan Bopanna and Sania Mirza in the second round on Saturday, after British No 1 Murray had earlier lost 6-4 to Gael Monfils in singles.

